{title: Life Of A Poor Boy}
{artist: Stonewall Jackson}
{composer: Written by E. C. (Mac) McCarty}

[G]When I was just a [C]youngster and [G]hardly in my [D7]teens
I [G]went to school on [C]many a day with [D7]faded old blue [G]jeans
The patches they were [C]many the [G]seat was all thread [D7]bare
But a [G]poor girl didn't [C]notice and a [D7]poor boy didn't [G]care
A poor boy don't [C]have no money a [D7]poor boy don't [G]have no dough
Give a poor boy a [C]pretty little girl and [G]watch that poor boy [D7]go
He's the [G]backbone of the [C]nation the [G]pappy of the [D7]land
With a [G]two buck loan he'll [C]build him a home
And [D7]raise him a poor boy [G]clan
His worries they are [C]many his [G]pleasures are but [D7]few
But [G]that don't worry a [C]poor boy his [D7]pappy had 'em [G]too
His living don't come [C]easy he [G]has to sweat it [D7]out
But [G]he'd rather be a [C]poor boy than a [D7]wealthy gad-a-[G]bout
